title: For Sale/Trade:  USMC ILBE Main backpack/bug out bag/hiking pack
postcontent: The ILBE pack was specially designed by Arc'teryx for the US Marines to provide a durable lightweight means of transporting gear in the field and works great for hiking, hunting or bugging out. This rugged Cordura 720 denier fabric pack is designed to carry a load of up to 120lbs while distributing the weight so it is still comfortable to wear. Heavy duty zippers on both sides allow access to the 4500 cu in. of interior space without unloading everything from the top. The comfortable internal frame has two metal ribs on the outer sides and two larger spars in the middle. The back of the pack offers MOLLE webbing for keeping all your gear close at hand but secure. There are multiple pockets on the exterior as well a holder that is compatible with a hydration system. Comes with lid/rainfly that covers the top of the pack using included clips. The lid also has a zippered pouch that can hold extra gear (room for 3 MRE's) as well as MOLLE webbing for securing even more gear. These genuine surplus packs are used but in good to very good condition. ------Does NOT come with BELT or RADIO POUCH.----- All zippers, snaps and clips are functional. Pack may have some signs of use and possibly some dust, dirt, scuffs, wear marks, small repairs, tape and or tape marks. These are great main packs and lids that Uncle Sam paid over $400 for and can be yours for a very low price.

Has the military acceptance proof marks of the eagle N, as well as the dot in a circle and the star on the takedown lever
Originally produced for the post war German Army or Police – then sold in the civilian market at German Racquet Sporting Clubs.
It is not imported, but brought here by someone who purchased it there.
Comes with the original box with matching serial number to the gun, manual, factory target, cleaning rod, an extra set of WWII grips, and three magazines. 
1962 West German Polizi leather holster
98% Bluing
Had to go to the Walther forums to research and find that the "One line slide" is very desirable to collectors.
This is made in between the P-38 and P-1 eras and is made with military parts
The value is put between $650-$750 and it will only go up in time.

This gun is pristine and I do not have to get rid of it - just seeing what is out there
